obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39765)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39765&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Probation of Offenders`
  line `Act, 1958.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in a State on such date as the State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different parts of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39766)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Now see Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39766&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898);`
  line
  line `(b) "probation officer" means an officer appointed to be a probation officer or recognised as such`
  line `under section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)^1, shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39767)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of court to release certain offenders after admonition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39767&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `When any person is found guilty`
  line `of having committed an offence punishable under section 379 or section 380 or section 381 or`
  line `section 404 or section 420 of the Indian Penal Code, (45 of 1860) or any offence punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for not more than two years, or with fine, or with both, under the Indian Penal Code or`
  line `any other law, and no previous conviction is proved against him and the court by which the person is`
  line `found guilty is of opinion that, having regard to the circumstances of the case including the nature of the`
  line `offence, and the character of the offender, it is expedient so to do, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, the court may, instead of sentencing him to any`
  line `punishment or releasing him on probation of good conduct under section 4, release him after due`
  line admonition.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, previous conviction against a person shall include any`
  line `previous order made against him under this section or section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39768)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of court to release certain offenders on probation of good conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39768&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any`
  line `person is found guilty of having committed an offence not punishable with death or imprisonment for life`
  line `and the court by which the person is found guilty is of opinion that, having regard to the circumstances of`
  line `the case including the nature of the offence and the character of the offender, it is expedient to release him`
  line `on probation of good conduct, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the court may, instead of sentencing him at once to any punishment direct that he be`
  line `released on his entering into a bond, with or without sureties, to appear and receive sentence when called`
  line `upon during such period, not exceeding three years, as the court may direct, and in the meantime to keep`
  line `the peace and be of good behaviour:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court shall not direct such release of an offender unless it is satisfied that the`
  line `offender or his surety, if any, has a fixed place of abode or regular occupation in the place over which the`
  line `court exercises jurisdiction or in which the offender is likely to live during the period for which he enters`
  line `into the bond.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making any order under sub-section (1), the court shall take into consideration the report,`
  line `if any, of the probation officer concerned in relation to the case.`
  line
  line `(3) When an order under sub-section (1) is made, the court may, if it is of opinion that in the interests`
  line `of the offender and of the public it is expedient so to do, in addition pass a supervision order directing that`
  line `the offender shall remain under the supervision of a probation officer named in the order during such`
  line `period, not being less than one year, as may be specified therein, and may in such supervision order`
  line `impose such conditions as it deems necessary for the due supervision of the offender.`
  line
  line `(4) The court making a supervision order under sub-section (3) shall require the offender, before he is`
  line `released, to enter into a bond, with or without sureties, to observe the conditions specified in such order`
  line `and such additional conditions with respect to residence, abstention from intoxicants or any other matter`
  line `as the court may, having regard to the particular circumstances, consider fit to impose for preventing a`
  line `repetition of the same offence or a commission of other offences by the offender.`
  line
  line `(5) The court making a supervision order under sub-section (3) shall explain to the offender the terms`
  line `and conditions of the order and shall forthwith furnish one copy of the supervision order to each of the`
  line `offenders, the sureties, if any, and the probation officer concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39769)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of court to require released offenders to pay compensation and costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39769&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The court`
  line `directing the release of an offender under section 3 or section 4, may, if it thinks fit, make at the same`
  line `time a further order directing him to pay—`
  line
  line `(a) such compensation as the court thinks reasonable for loss or injury caused to any person by`
  line `the commission of the offence; and`
  line
  line `(b) such costs of the proceedings as the court thinks reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount ordered to be paid under sub-section (1) may be recovered as a fine in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of sections 386 and 387 of the Code.`
  line
  line `(3) A civil court trying any suit, arising out of the same matter for which the offender is`
  line `prosecuted, shall take into account any amount paid or recovered as compensation under sub-section (1)`
  line `in awarding damages.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39770)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Restrictions on imprisonment of offenders under twenty-one years of age.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39770&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any`
  line `person under twenty-one years of age is found guilty of having committed an offence punishable with`
  line `imprisonment (but not with imprisonment for life), the court by which the person is found guilty shall not`
  line `sentence him to imprisonment unless it is satisfied that, having regard to the circumstances of the case`
  line `including the nature of the offence and the character of the offender, it would not be desirable to deal`
  line `with him under section 3 or section 4, and if the court passes any sentence of imprisonment on the`
  line `offender, it shall record its reasons for doing so.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of satisfying itself whether it would not be desirable to deal under section 3 or`
  line `section 4 with an offender referred to in sub-section (1), the court shall call for a report from the probation`
  line `officer and consider the report, if any, and any other information available to it relating to the character`
  line `and physical and mental condition of the offender.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39771)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Report of probation officer to be confidential.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39771&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The report of a probation officer referred to`
  line `in sub-section (2) of section 4 or sub-section (2) of section 6 shall be treated as confidential:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, if it so thinks fit, communicate the substance thereof to the offender and`
  line `may give him an opportunity of producing such evidence as may be relevant to the matter stated in`
  line `the report.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39772)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Variation of conditions of probation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39772&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on the application of a probation officer, any court`
  line `which passes an order under section 4 in respect of an offender is of opinion that in the interests of the`
  line `offender and the public it is expedient or necessary to vary the conditions of any bond entered into by the`
  line `offender, it may, at any time during the period when the bond is effective, vary the bond by extending or`
  line `diminishing the duration thereof so, however, that it shall not exceed three years from the date of the`
  line `original order or by altering the conditions thereof or by inserting additional conditions therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such variation shall be made without giving the offender and the surety or`
  line `sureties mentioned in the bond an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) If any surety refuses to consent to any variation proposed to be made under sub-section (1), the`
  line `court may require the offender to enter into a fresh bond and if the offender refuses or fails to do so, the`
  line `court may sentence him for the offence of which he was found guilty.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, the court which passes an order under`
  line `section 4 in respect of an offender may, if it is satisfied on an application made by the probation officer,`
  line `that the conduct of the offender has been such as to make it unnecessary that he should be kept any longer`
  line `under supervision, discharge the bond or bonds entered into by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39773)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure in case of offender failing to observe conditions of bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39773&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the court which`
  line `passes an order under section 4 in respect of an offender or any court which could have dealt with the`
  line `offender in respect of his original offence has reason to believe, on the report of a probation officer`
  line `or otherwise, that the offender has failed to observe any of the conditions of the bond or bonds entered`
  line `into by him, it may issue a warrant for his arrest or may, if it thinks fit, issue a summons to him and his`
  line `sureties, if any, requiring him or them to attend before it at such time as may be specified in the summons.`
  line
  line `(2) The court before which an offender is so brought or appears may either remand him to custody`
  line `until the case is concluded or it may grant him bail, with or without surety, to appear on the date which it`
  line `may fix for hearing.`
  line
  line `(3) If the court, after hearing the case, is satisfied that the offender has failed to observe any of the`
  line `conditions of the bond or bonds entered into by him, it may forthwith—`
  line
  line `(a) sentence him for the original offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the failure is for the first time, then, without prejudice to the continuance in force of the`
  line `bond, impose upon him a penalty not exceeding fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) If a penalty imposed under clause (b) of sub-section (3) is not paid within such period as the court`
  line `may fix, the court may sentence the offender for the original offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39774)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Provision as to sureties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39774&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 122, 126, 126A, 406A, 514, 514A, 514B`
  line `and 515 of the Code shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of bonds and sureties given under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39784)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Courts competent to make order under the Act, appeal and revision and powers of courts in appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39784&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code or any other law, an order`
  line `under this Act, may be made by any court empowered to try and sentence the offender to imprisonment`
  line `and also by the High Court or any other court when the case comes before it on appeal or in revision.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, where an order under section 3 or section 4 is`
  line `made by any court trying the offender (other than a High Court), an appeal shall lie to the court to which`
  line `appeals ordinarily lie from the sentences of the former court.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case where any person under twenty-one years of age is found guilty of having committed`
  line `an offence and the court by which he is found guilty declines to deal with him under section 3 or`
  line `section 4, and passes against him any sentence of imprisonment with or without fine from which no`
  line `appeal lies or is preferred, then, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code or any other law, the`
  line `court to which appeals ordinarily lie from the sentences of the former court may, either of its own motion`
  line `or on an application made to it by the convicted person or the probation officer, call for and examine the`
  line `record of the case and pass such order thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) When an order has been made under section 3 or section 4 in respect of an offender, the Appellate`
  line `Court or the High Court in the exercise of its power of revision may set aside such order and in lieu`
  line `thereof pass sentence on such offender according to law:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Court or the High Court in revision shall not inflict a greater punishment`
  line `than might have been inflicted by the court by which the offender was found guilty.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39776)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Removal of disqualification attaching to conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39776&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other law, a person found guilty of an offence and dealt with under the provisions of section 3 or`
  line `section 4 shall not suffer disqualification, if any, attaching to a conviction of an offence under such law:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a person who, after his release under section 4 is`
  line `subsequently sentenced for the original offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39777)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Probation officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39777&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A probation officer under this Act shall be—`
  line
  line `(a) a person appointed to be a probation officer by the State Government or recognised as such by`
  line `the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) a person provided for this purpose by a society recognised in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) In any exceptional case, any other person who, in the opinion of the court, is fit to act as a`
  line `probation officer in the special circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(2) A court which passes an order under section 4 or the district magistrate of the district in which the`
  line `offender for the time being resides may, at any time, appoint any probation officer in the place of the`
  line `person named in the supervision order.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, a presidency town shall be deemed to be a district and`
  line `chief presidency magistrate shall be deemed to be the district magistrate of that district.`
  line
  line `(3) A probation officer, in the exercise of his duties under this Act, shall be subject to the control of`
  line `the district magistrate of the district in which the offender for the time being resides.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39778)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Duties of probation officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39778&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `A probation officer shall, subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions, as may be prescribed,—`
  line
  line `(a) inquire, in accordance with any directions of a court, into the circumstances or home`
  line `surroundings of any person accused of an offence with a view to assist the court in determining the`
  line `most suitable method of dealing with him and submit reports to the court;`
  line
  line `(b) supervise probationers and other persons placed under his supervision and, where necessary,`
  line `endeavour to find them suitable employment;`
  line
  line `(c) advise and assist offenders in the payment of compensation or costs ordered by the Court;`
  line
  line `(d) advise and assist, in such cases and in such manner as may be prescribed, persons who have`
  line `been released under section 4; and`
  line
  line `(e) perform such other duties as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39779)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Probation officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39779&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every probation officer and every other officer`
  line `appointed in pursuance of this Act shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39780)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39780&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `State Government or any probation officer or any other officer appointed under this Act in respect of`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules`
  line `or orders made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39781)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39781&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) appointment of probation officers, the terms and conditions of their service and the area`
  line `within which they are to exercise jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(b) duties of probation officers under this Act and the submission of reports by them;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions on which societies may be recognised for the purposes of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) the payment of remuneration and expenses to probation officers or of a subsidy to any society`
  line `which provides probation officers; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be subject to the condition of previous publication`
  line `and shall, as soon as may be after they are made, be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39782)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Saving of operation of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1 The words and figures “or the Suppression of Immoral Traffic in Women and Girls Act, 1956” omitted by Act 46 of 1978, s. 20 (w.e.f. 2-1-1979).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39782&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the provisions of`
  line `section 31 of the Reformatory Schools Act, 1897 (8 of 1897), or sub-section (2) of section 5 of the`
  line `Prevention of Corruption Act, 1947 (2 of 1947), ^1`
  line `* * * or of any law in force in any State relating to`
  line `juvenile offenders or Borstal Schools.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39783)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Section 562 of the Code not to apply in certain areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214&sectionId=39783&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00003_195820_1517807319214
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 18 section 562 of the Code shall cease to apply to the States or parts thereof in which this Act is`
  line `brought into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
